President Donald J. Trump has signed a proclamation recognizing Manufacturing Day as an annual celebration on the first Friday of October. Manufacturing Day aims to highlight the development in manufacturing nationwide and provide an opportunity for American manufacturers to educate their communities about career opportunities in manufacturing. The President emphasized that his administration's deregulation initiatives will promote job creation and economic growth in the manufacturing sector. The proclamation signing took place in the Oval Office and was attended by Cabinet members, representatives from manufacturers across the country, and the President and CEO of the National Association of Manufacturers (NAM). Attendees expressed their support for manufacturing, with one executive stating that manufacturing is the backbone of America.